# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Quick Start

```bash
# Backend
make dev                                    # → :8080 (requires Go & PostgreSQL)

# Web UI ([[.UIDir]]/)
cd [[.UIDir]] && npm install && npm run dev  # → :5173 (proxies /api → :8080)

# Desktop (Tauri — optional)
cd [[.DesktopDir]] && npm install && npm run tauri dev

# Mini-program (Taro — optional)
cd [[.MiniappDir]] && npm install && npm run dev:weapp
```

## Architecture

This is a **mozi-builder-based** project: the mozi model-driven development platform
is embedded via `github.com/pangu-studio/mozi-builder/devplatform`. Business models
are defined using the mozi modeling framework (via `mozi` CLI or the integrated
dev-platform UI), and code is generated through AI Coding change plans.

**Stack**: Go + Gin (HTTP) + mozi-builder (dev platform)
**Future**: Ent (ORM) will be added when the first business model is generated.

### Key environment variables

| Variable | Default | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `[[.AddrEnv]]` | `:8080` | Server listen address |
| `[[.DevPlatformEnv]]` | `false` | Enable dev-platform API (`true`/`1` to enable) |
| `MOZI_DB` | `postgres://localhost:5432/[[.ModuleBase]]_design?sslmode=disable` | Design database DSN |
| `[[.AdminPathEnv]]` | `[[.UIDir]]/dist` | Web UI build output directory |
| `[[.BuilderTokenEnv]]` | `dev` | Builder access token (placeholder; replace in prod) |

### Endpoints (day 1)

| Method | Path | Auth | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|---------|
| `GET` | `/api/ping` | — | Health check |
| `*` | `/dev-platform/*` | Builder | Mozi dev platform API (when `[[.DevPlatformEnv]]=true`) |
| `*` | `/admin/*` | — | Web UI SPA static files |

### Adding your first model

1. Start PostgreSQL and set `MOZI_DB` in `.env`.
2. `mozi init` — initializes the design database.
3. Model your domain via the `mozi` CLI or the integrated dev-platform UI at `http://localhost:8080/admin/dev-platform`.
4. `mozi change-plan --model <Module/Model>` — get an AI Coding contract.
5. Apply the change plan to generate Ent schemas, handlers, and UI pages.
6. `make generate && cd [[.UIDir]] && npm run build && cd .. && make build`.

For detailed mozi workflow documentation, see `docs/dev-platform-guide.md` and the
[mozi-builder skills/mozi/SKILL.md](https://github.com/pangu-studio/mozi-builder/blob/main/skills/mozi/SKILL.md) skill file.
